<TITLE> Newsprint import duty cuts proposed </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jun 7 (bdnews24.com) - The government has finally proposed bringing down the import duty on newsprint from the existing 25 percent to 15 percent responding to a long-standing demand of the newspaper industry. "I propose reduction of customs duty on the import of newsprint considering the problems of the newspaper industry," said finance and planning adviser AB Mirza Md Azizul Islam in his budget proposals for FY 2007-08 Thursday. The adviser also offered duty-free import of newsprint raw materials to develop the local newsprint industry. The new measure would also help reduce expenses on education. Newspaper Owners Association of Bangladesh had several times in the past demanded that the government slash the import duty on the item amid its price hike in the global market. Imported newsprint constitutes about 75 percent of the local requirement, the remainder comes locally. bd
